Nigerian tomato stew is a major favourite in most homes as it can be eaten with almost any meal from rice to beans to traditional swallow. You don’t have to give up in this favourite Nigerian tomato stew because of health or weight reason rather switch to the oil-less tomato stew. The oil-less tomato stew option is a delight to taste even without “oil”. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-838480 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Tomato-stew-with-beans-and-bread-Photo-ichef-bbci.jpg" alt="" width="1000" height="563" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Tomato-stew-with-beans-and-bread-Photo-ichef-bbci.jpg 832w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Tomato-stew-with-beans-and-bread-Photo-ichef-bbci-640x360.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Tomato-stew-with-beans-and-bread-Photo-ichef-bbci-320x180.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Tomato-stew-with-beans-and-bread-Photo-ichef-bbci-281x158.jpg 281w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Tomato-stew-with-beans-and-bread-Photo-ichef-bbci-562x316.jpg 562w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Tomato-stew-with-beans-and-bread-Photo-ichef-bbci-531x299.jpg 531w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Tomato-stew-with-beans-and-bread-Photo-ichef-bbci-1062x598.jpg 1062w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Tomato-stew-with-beans-and-bread-Photo-ichef-bbci-487x274.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Tomato-stew-with-beans-and-bread-Photo-ichef-bbci-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" />